Oil Extends Losses for Fifth Day; Heads for Biggest Weekly Drop Since 2008

-- B y   S t e p h e n   V o s s
-- 
2011-05-06T07:45:13Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-06/oil-extends-losses-for-fifth-day-heads-for-biggest-weekly-drop-since-2008.html
Oil extended declines in  New York ,
falling for a fifth day and headed for its biggest weekly
decline since December 2008 on concern fuel demand will slow
after reports indicated economic weakness in the U.S. and
Europe.  Crude for June delivery dropped as much as $3.30, or 3.3
percent, to $96.50 a barrel in electronic trading on the  New
York Mercantile Exchange . It earlier gained as much as $1.15 to
$100.95 a barrel.  Yesterday, oil futures fell $9.44 to $99.80, the lowest
since March 16 and the biggest percentage drop since April 20,
2009.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stephen Voss in London at 
